      • trimCache

        public static void trimCache(Context context,
                             int limitSize)
        Trim the SDoc cache files to specified size.
        Parameters:
        context - The Context for your application.
        limitSize - The specified cache size. The unit is MB. If cache size is too small, then SDoc performance is low. If cache size is too big, then waste device storage. The minimum size is 200 MB, and maximum size is 500 MB. If smaller than 200 MB, it change to 200 MB. If bigger than 500 MB, it change to 500 MB.
